# Code owners for the isms repository.
#
# Single-maintainer scale (GOVERNANCE.md "Maintainer authority"). The
# maintainer owns the framework and all control-of-controls paths. Instance
# content (instance/, except the control-of-controls files listed below) is
# operational and owned by the deploying organisation, so it is intentionally
# left without a global owner here.
#
# Control-of-controls paths (CLAUDE.md Hard Rule 5, DOC-005, DOC-002) require
# maintainer review on every change.

# Framework, tooling, repo-level docs, and CI default to the maintainer.
*                                           @rmednitzer

# Control-of-controls: signing registry, CI, ownership, schemas, validators.
/.gitsigners                                @rmednitzer
/.github/                                   @rmednitzer
/.github/CODEOWNERS                         @rmednitzer
/.github/workflows/                         @rmednitzer
/tooling/schemas/                           @rmednitzer
/tooling/validators/                        @rmednitzer

# Framework authority surfaces (GOVERNANCE.md, DOC-001, SOP-101..103).
/framework-refs/sources/registry.yaml       @rmednitzer
/framework-refs/calendar/                   @rmednitzer
/template/                                  @rmednitzer

# Instance control-of-controls (roles and separation of duties only).
/instance/users/roles.yaml                  @rmednitzer
/instance/users/separation-of-duties.yaml   @rmednitzer
